Installation
============

First, install prerequisites::

    $ pip install flask, pymongo, Flask-RESTful

Flask==0.10.1
Flask-RESTful==0.2.12

Then, you can clone the repo as follows::

    $ git clone git@bitbucket.org:aschuth/ll-challenge.git

Building Documentation
----------------------

In case you also want to rebuild the documentation, you will need the following::

    $ pip install sphinx, sphinx_bootstrap_theme

Additionally, Flask Sphinx support is needed::

    $ hg clone ssh://hg@bitbucket.org/birkenfeld/sphinx-contrib
    $ cd sphinx-contrib
    $ python setup.py build
    $ sudo python setup.py install

To build the docs::
    
    $ cd docs
    $ make html

The documentation will appear in docs/build/html.
